Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 1
Create Matrix IoT Gateway
1
Open your browser and navigate to: "https://IP_Data_Collector/". You can also use
the a4conf icon on the Data Collector desktop.
2
Click "Data-Collector" within the main menu.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 2
3
Select "Kepware".
4
Move to "Create IoT Gateway".
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 3
5
Select a Kepware Channel and click on it to expand its menu.
6
Choose "Matrix".
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 4
7
Fill in the "Machine ID" field. If you have already added machine serial numbers in
the "Data Collector -> Kepware -> Local Thing" tab, you can select them
automatically.
8
Fill in the "Blob Folder" field. This is the folder on the Blob Storage to which the
files containing the tags will be sent within the IoT Gateway being created.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 5
9
The "Scan rate" field allows you to change the scan rate interval time.
10
The "Publish rate" field allows you to change the frequency at which data is sent to
the Data Sender.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 6
11
The "Sampling time" field allows you to specify how often the matrix to be created
in the IoT Gateway will be automically modified on the source (PLC/HMI/...).
12
The "Sampling index" field allows you to change the sampling index. This number
indicates the initial index used to create the matrix.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 7
13
The "Sampling number" field allows you to change the number of rows in the
matrix.
14
Click the "Create" button if you want to create an IoT Gateway without selecting
specifics tags, by default they are all selected.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 8
15
Select the "Choose tags" checkbox if you want to choose specific tags.
16
Then click the "Create" button.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 9
17
Click on the little "arrow" on the left to expand the folder and tick all the tags (or
folders) you want to use.
18
Click the "greater than" button between "Channel" and "IoT Gateway", after you
finished choosing the tags (or folders) you need.
Made with Scribe - https://scribehow.com 10
19
Click the "Create IoT Gateway" button to complete the operation.
20
You can now click the "Close" button.
